snippet: The kidnapping and release of Prime Minister Ali Zeidan on Thursday underscored the unrivaled authority of militias in Libya after the fall of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.
abstract: Kidnapping and release of Libyan Prime Minister Ali Zeidan underscores unrivaled authority of militias in country after the fall of Col Muammar el-Qaddafi; militia members in Tripoli fill gap left by weak central government, and many throughout Libya are loyal only to their own commanders.

byline.contributor: David D. Kirkpatrick contributed reporting from Cairo, and Suliman Ali Zway from Tripoli, Libya.

lead_paragraph: The kidnapping and release of Prime Minister Ali Zeidan on Thursday underscored the unrivaled authority of militias in Libya after the fall of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi.

headline.main: Show of Power by Libya Militia in Kidnapping
headline.print_headline: Show of Power By Libya Militia In Kidnapping
